page.title: 11ECOLOGY OF NORTH HYKEHAM
page.content: The large amount of inland water attracts many different kinds of birds. There are mallard,grebe,swans,tufted duck, moorhens and coot.The banks provide nesting places. There also are finches,sparrows, starlings,bluetits,chaffinches, robins, gulls,pigeons,thrushes, and owls,to mention some of those more frequently seen. In the summer they are joined by swallows,martins,swifts and the often heard but seldom seen,cuckoo. We take the birds for granted as everyday occurences.We can see woodpeckers,skylarks,magpies and yellow hammers too. As well as birds there are gamebirds,rabbits,squirrels and foxes in the woods.
